Why it is called psuedo-class?
A CSS pseudo-class is a keyword added to a selector that specifies a special state of the selected element. 
It apply some special property which css element can not apply it.
For example, the pseudo-class :hover can be used to select a button when a user's pointer hovers over the button and this selected button can then be styled.

button:hover {
  color: blue;
}
When user hover the button its color become blue.
:autofill
:hover
:enabled
:read-only
