what are gradient in CSS
CSS gradients is display smooth transitions between two or more specified colors.
Thier are 3 types

linear gradient:: A linear gradient creates a band of colors that progress in a straight line.
To create a linear gradient you must define at least two color stops. 

Radial gradients::You can also make them circular or elliptical.
 conic-gradient :: you need to create a conic gradient are two colors.
 
 -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 Transition
 It allows you to change property values smoothly, over a given duration.
 If the duration part is not specified, the transition will have no effect, because the default value is 0.
 It is a way of changing the CSS property with animation. We can define the speed.
 
transition
transition-delay
transition-duration
transition-property
transition-timing-function
